    "narrative": "The Austin Waves roster is primed for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by the favorable matchups for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.92) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56). Both benefit significantly from facing weak starters, as **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** looks to capitalize on a +19% skill adjustment against a 5.35 xERA, while **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** pairs a similar skill advantage with a +14% boost from his platoon dynamic. **Kyle Tucker** (73.43) remains an anchor in our 5x5 strategy; while his park factor is slightly negative, his projected output remains elite due to his consistent presence in the two-hole. We are also monitoring the high-upside play of **Jackson Merrill** (70.77), whose +14% park factor adjustment makes him a standout against the opposing rotation.\n\nThe primary roster exclusion for today is **Nolan Schanuel**, who narrowly missed the cut with a 57.27 score. While his matchup against a 4.42 xERA pitcher offers a solid floor, the optimizer prioritized the aggressive stacking of high-efficiency hitters against the softer arms we are attacking elsewhere. On the risk front, **Luis Robert Jr.** (52.42) remains a volatile start; while he provides necessary SB potential, his -15% platoon adjustment and the opponent\u2019s ability to hold runners (61% SB suppression) significantly depress his score. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** (54.01) faces a daunting matchup against a lefty, and while his order placement saves him from the bench, his efficiency is hampered by the opposing pitcher's elite pickoff/hold capability. We will look for **Marcell Ozuna** (59.22) to provide stability in the UTIL spot, as his base projection remains high enough to weather the lack of additional platoon support.",
